5. Live Monitor Dashboard (cogs/live_monitor.py) License and Identity Protection

The Live Monitor Dashboard, including but not limited to its name, branding,
identity, and Credits tab, is NOT covered by the MIT License governing the
remainder of the Software and is separately copyrighted.

Protected components include, but are not limited to:
- The names “Zoryx”, “Zoryx Framework”, and “Zoryx Discord Bot Framework”
- The author name “TheHolyOneZ”
- The Live Monitor Dashboard Credits tab, including its layout, wording,
  structure, and crown SVG artwork

The Credits tab MUST:
- Remain clearly visible at all times
- Remain unaltered in wording, layout, and visual design
- Not be hidden, removed, renamed, duplicated, repositioned, minimized,
  or visually obscured in any way

Users ARE permitted to:
- Customize styling, layout, or functionality of the dashboard outside
  the protected Credits section
- Extend the dashboard with new features, integrations, or additional tabs

If a new tab is added, it MUST:
- Be clearly labeled as the modifier’s own work
- Accurately describe the modifications or additions made
- Include wording such as:
  “Tab created by <YourName>. Added custom functionality on top of the existing Zoryx system.”

Users MUST NOT:
- Claim authorship of framework code or systems they did not create
- Present themselves as the original creator of the framework
- Imply ownership of backend logic they did not meaningfully modify
- Modify backend logic in a way that introduces security risks
- Remove, obscure, or misrepresent attribution to the original author
- Modify the framework with intent to mislead, damage reputation,
  or misrepresent authorship

Any violation of this section constitutes a breach of license and intent,
unless explicit, direct permission is granted by TheHolyOneZ.



THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR
